The Kaduna State Government has disclosed that bandits have killed five people in Igabi and Chikun Local Government Areas (LGAs) of the state. Mr Samuel Aruwan, the State’s Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, stated this in a statement on Saturday. Aruwan reported that the bandits killed two persons in Chikun LGA and razed two buildings including a place of worship in the area. Kaduna: Bandits kill four in Igabi, Jema’a LGAs, three others sustain injuries According to him, the other three were killed at Lambar Zango area along the Kaduna-Zaria Road in Igabi LGA. The commissioner said Governor Nasir El-Rufai had consoled the families of the victims. He added that the governor also prayed God to grant the deceased eternal rest. Kaduna bandits attack: Eight killed, four injured in Kajuru, Giwa, Chikun LGAs